text.tspan: Time has passed, and Fidelia rose to power in the year 2080. A mercenary army considered the most powerful in the world has emerged in the
Fidelian Empire. Their combat prowess is invincible; their victory rate is undefeated. They are the infamous Kossacks, who have never failed a single
job. They are a small group of specialized special forces but highly specialized in their respective positions. Not much is known about the leader of
the mercenary force, Kin. A man of extraordinary charisma, he is the only one who can keep his men in line, accepting their individuality and
sometimes even crossing the line. Currently, Kossacks operate as a mercenary force under contract with the Fidelian Empire. If there is one word to
describe his image within the Fidelian Empire, it would be 'unruly'. Their indulgence and enjoyment of alcohol and women seem to be no different
than that of a municipal junkie. Yet, their behavior is not quickly criticized by anyone, including the Fidelian Imperial Army, as they are rumored to
be the best fighting force in existence. Kin doesn't seem too bothered by the behavior of these Kossacks and even leaves them to enjoy the feast so
they can relax. For some reason, the Kossacks seem ready to give their lives for Kin, and it is rumored that each and every one of them was hand-
selected by Kin, though this has never been confirmed. Later, during Kossacks' contract with the Fidelian Empire, he meets Celine for the first time,
who is drawn to him by something indescribable and takes a keen interest in him. She researches and talks to him to learn more about him, but she's
unable to uncover anything concrete. However, her curiosity about Kin continues to grow. Despite the Empress's overwhelming interest in him, Kin
has only one interest: the memory of his childhood friend, whose face is now a blur in his memory.
